name: integer_u64_u32_maximum
description: |
  This is u32 maximum represented as u64. It is the last value that
  survives narrowing to u32; the paired next value requires bit 32
  and exposes truncation, masking, and arithmetic performed at the wrong width.
format: hex
decode-as: u64-le
pair:
  - with: ../u32/maximum.input
    hint: equal
  - with: above-u32-maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u64"
  - "lower-width"
  - "maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "narrowing"
  - "truncation"
---
ff ff ff ff 00 00 00 00   # 4294967295
